review_blob: Less than $7 bucks a 12 pack and better than most big name light beers, so I will not dog it to much ;-) But if I were going to buy a light beer without money as a factor I would for sure get Sam Adams light!

Not that bad. I got it on sale for 5.99 at Kroger, so I gave it a shot because Sweetwater 420 is 8.99 a six pack. I can say it is not hoppy enough to be a PA but it is not that bad. Pours a 1/2" head with more of a malt flavor than a hoppy flavor which is strange since the bottle reads"Enjoyably Hoppy" with a picture of a frog on the bottle to prove it! (dont look at the pic on this page it is out-dated). I might would buy it again if it stays at a low price. On second thought, I will stick with Sweetwater 420 or SN.

Bland & water like, but a step-up from Bud so I may try getting my friends to try it so I dont have to see those King of Beer bottles in my trash anymore!

Its not that bad, but I will take their Ranger IPA any day other this (and yes, I know this is not an IPA)  Sweetwater 420 - Drinkem If You Gotem!!!

OK, I thought this was a heavy beer when I was younger??? I dont know if they changed it or I just have better taste now? Anyway, it is better than Bud Lite & Miller Lite so, it could be worse... (I keep it in the fridge for my rookie fam & friends because they cant handle my Sweetwater 420 ;-)
Head fades quickly with your standard gold appearance. Great hop flavor with a bitter after taste. Citrus & pine aroma. Great IPA & Im glad I got it at Kroger in their pick six deal they have!
Just the right amount of hops & malt. Pours a half inch head with a citrus & pine aroma. This is my number one Pale Ale & is my daily. Drinkem if you gotem!
